Use the below regex commands to check for and replace SKIP codes in a stock KANJIDIC.

To search for lines containing SKIP codes/miscodes:
grep -e ' [[:alpha:]]*P[[:digit:]]\+-[[:digit:]]\+-[[:digit:]]\+ ' < kanjidic

To remove SKIP codes/miscodes:
sed -e 's/ [[:alpha:]]*P[[:digit:]]\+-[[:digit:]]\+-[[:digit:]]\+ / /' < kanjidic.src > kanjidic.dest
NOTE: it takes a total of 7 passes to get rid of all codes.  After 7 passes, verify using the above grep command.
